<TITLE> Bush's mother hospitalized due stomach pains </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HOUSTON, Wed Nov 26, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Barbara Bush, mother of President George W Bush, was hospitalized on Tuesday after complaining of stomach pains, a family spokesman said. Mrs. Bush, 83, went to Methodist Hospital in Houston for tests, said Jim Appleby, a spokesman for former President George H W Bush, her husband and father of President Bush. Appleby declined to give further details. Local news station KHOU reported that former President Bush accompanied his wife to the hospital, and that she will likely be released from hospital late Tuesday or early Wednesday
